Win32 Build Instructions
========================

Setup
-----

build-tree
	alsp_src
	mwbuild
	tcltk_interface
	alsdev

Build
-----

Make "alspro x86.lib" in the mwbuild directory.

In alsdev, setup an alsdir with the folders "builtins" and "library".  Add
"shared" and "image" as described in the Runtime section below.

Open win32_alsdev.mcp, and make "Win32 Build" to create "ALS Prolog Base.exe"

Create a new image from "ALS Prolog Base.exe" with the following command:

save_image('ALS Prolog', [select_lib(builtins, [debugger,blt_dvsh]),
	select_lib(library,[miscterm,strctutl,strings,tcl_sppt,tk_alslib, listutl1])]).


Runtime Setup
-------------

Here is the minimal runtime setup.  Optional additions are alsdir/library, examples, etc.

ALS Prolog.exe
tcl8.0.dll
tk8.0.dll
cw3215.dll
lib // The Tcl/Tk lib folder
alsdir
	shared
		debugwin.tcl
		als_menu.tcl
		als_settings.tcl
		als_tklib.tcl
		alsdev.tcl
		alsdev_main.tcl
		als_document.tcl
		defstr.tcl
	image
		als_splash.tcl
		down-arrow-blue.gif
		left-arrow-blue.gif
		right-arrow-blue.gif
		turnstile_splash.gif
		up-arrow-blue.gif

